Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.32,0:00:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please enjoy your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.11,0:00:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.08,0:00:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I just didn't think you literally meant tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.04,0:00:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It's my treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Nakajou's theory didn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.68,0:00:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Haba's?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.02,0:00:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about Sawakiguchi's?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.49,0:00:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid it was no good either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.36,0:00:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.38,0:00:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.58,0:00:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No need for formalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.95,0:00:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I would like to hear what was wrong with their theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.16,0:00:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Firstly, the problem with Nakajou's theory was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.99,0:00:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.86,0:00:58.33,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,250)}Bored, sitting on the windowsill,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.33,0:01:06.46,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,250)}I frown at the wind to hide my awkwardness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.67,0:01:14.55,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(280,0)\blur3\t(0,989,2,\blur0.5)}Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:19.64,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,250)}I nod uncertainly as I shape
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.97,0:01:25.35,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,the future in my hands feeling mighty
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.35,0:01:30.52,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,250)}I feel that the wind is bringing change
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.90,0:01:35.61,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's your fault for calling out to my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.37,0:01:42.70,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,250)}The cloudy sky tells a tale of what's to come
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.70,0:01:51.21,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)}Spread our wings with more courage than ever before
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.21,0:01:55.80,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,Light and dark are still vague in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:02:02.10,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,but still we want to know the reason behind kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.10,0:02:06.64,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,No one so far has ever reached
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.64,0:02:09.52,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,the shining distance far beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:18.11,OP,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,350)}Let's get there before the past takes it all
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.95,0:02:22.91,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\xshad-2\yshad-1\fs50\blur0.8\fnSuplexmentary Comic NC\c&H365146&\4c&HBDDFCC&\pos(602,410)}Tea Shop \N1-2-3
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:22.91,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\xshad2\yshad1\fs50\blur0.8\fnSuplexmentary Comic NC\c&H365146&\4c&H2F4238&\pos(602,410)}Tea Shop \N1-2-3
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.91,0:02:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why Sawakiguchi's theory doesn't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:32.67,ep title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(859,309)\blur3\bord1\clip(586,554,603,599)\t(109,800,\clip(586,554,1280,599)\t(3821,4200,\clip(1280,554,1280,599)))\pos(1026,557)}Out of Sight, Out of Mind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.80,0:02:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who refuted Nakajou's theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.52,0:02:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.30,0:02:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As well as Haba's and Sawakiguchi's?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.96,0:02:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.46,0:02:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked you to solve this mystery, you told me not to have weird expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you have refuted all their theories –\N just as I secretly expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You expected this to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.81,0:02:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't cut out for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.95,0:03:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been clear to me from the beginning that they lack the skills necessary to solve this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.31,0:03:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this was all a charade? Then—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.05,0:03:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm not saying they are talentless. They all have valuable skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But those skills are of no use to them in solving this difficult—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without your assistance, we would need to accept one of their theories instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.65,0:03:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the project would fail in the worst possible way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're cold and realistic. A bit too much so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If required, I can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have one person on whom I can place my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard of his skill from three persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One is Chitanda Eru. One is someone from outside the school{his sister}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last is Tougaito Masashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person would be our best choice to play the detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or so we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, not the Classics Club, who I've been after from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.58,0:03:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.38,0:04:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you have already proven your abilities in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.17,0:04:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.66,0:04:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask you once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.70,0:04:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, please lend class 2-F your aid,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.80,0:04:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and find the solution to our movie's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.80,0:04:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have that kind of skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Please listen to my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.45,0:04:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a certain sports club there was a substitute player.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.03,0:04:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She trained as hard as she could to become a full player, but she was never allowed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.98,0:04:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was because the club had many other people with much more skill than she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:05:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was even one player who could only be described as a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.11,0:05:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Needless to say, the difference between her and the genius was like night and day.
Dialogue: 7,0:05:04.78,0:05:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The genius did so well in a competition that she was named MVP.{no idea what that is}{most valuable player}
