Dialogue: 1,0:15:06.19,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one of the six characters could have taken the master key from the office and entered the corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.88,0:15:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the culprit wasn't one of those six, there's only one explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.21,0:15:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must have been a seventh person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.76,0:15:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A seventh person? Like Sawakiguchi predicted?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first it sounded pretty ridiculous,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.91,0:15:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if what she said is correct, Hongou was looking for a seventh actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remembering that was what cemented this idea in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.37,0:15:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongou wrote this script according to the rules, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.60,0:15:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'd have some kind of slasher pop up out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.01,0:15:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were a few more things in the video that didn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi noted them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.74,0:16:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Kounosu finds the floor plan, it's lit up. Probably from a flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, when they go to look for Kaitou...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.94,0:16:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The corridor is dim and poorly lit. They use a flashlight there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.19,0:16:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flashlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.81,0:16:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But none of the main actors carried one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see this from the scenes right after it's used,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.06,0:16:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for instance when they first enter the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.28,0:16:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They had time to hide the flashlight, but there'd be no logical reason for them to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, you can say that it's just a matter of lighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.32,0:16:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that, please keep this in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is something I'm saying as a movie enthusiast, so please don't be offended.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.44,0:16:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This movie is boring. The acting is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.01,0:16:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera work in particular is extremely amateurish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.29,0:16:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that was on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cameraman was filming from the six actors' point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you get it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.29,0:17:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cameraman was the seventh actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.35,0:17:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were seven of them from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.18,0:17:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The six actors who appeared on screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the cameraman who filmed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seven in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this. The actors glance at the camera every now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.92,0:17:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's not safe to sleep here—{overlap with prev line}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.24,0:17:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are conscious of the camera's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.80,0:17:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not right to call him the cameraman, so let's call him the seventh character.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.45,0:17:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not unusual to consider there'd be someone holding that flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.23,0:17:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera work is bad because he can't film the same scene from various points of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.58,0:17:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes sense to consider him an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And here's the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera stayed in the lobby until everyone else left, then the scene was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.56,0:18:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which meant that the camera was stopped and left waiting for the others to return to the lobby.{goes over a scene change, can't be helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.90,0:18:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the crime is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character waited for everyone else to vanish into the theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stopped the camera, quickly took the master key from the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.41,0:18:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,killed Kaitou, then locked the room using the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.06,0:18:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he waited in the lobby for the others to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.49,0:18:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hongou has yet to choose a seventh actor, I'd suggest you do so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.64,0:18:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.05,0:18:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Firstly, if this character existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't it be strange that he never says a word, and none of the others speak to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.26,0:18:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongou might've considered that as the motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character is always ignored by the other six.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.80,0:18:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why he never talked to them, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.22,0:19:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Secondly, the people in the theater would be able to figure this out instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely anyone would suspect this seventh character who supposedly stayed in the lobby all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.45,0:19:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention that the second "locked room"\N you mentioned is still a factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.26,0:19:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume that the actors could see the seventh character moving around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the culprit would be obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Sawakiguchi would put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.53,0:19:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who cares about a witness or two?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes no difference if the characters figure it out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.07,0:19:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The important part is making the viewers wonder about the mystery, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's why there's no detective role in the script itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because the culprit is clear to the characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without them even having to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:20:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've solved Hongou's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.62,0:20:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was somewhat taken aback by your daring conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but as it fits all the facts, it must be right.{yeah right}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And... thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.65,0:20:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can finally complete the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.08,0:20:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.10,0:20:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.94,0:20:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A power possessed by no other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you decide the title of the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.15,0:20:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.15,0:20:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd all be happy with any idea you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Something that fits the movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.70,0:20:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about "Out of Sight, Out of Mind"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a great title! Let's go with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.69,0:21:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Home run.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone in third year...{teacher}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.63,0:21:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the culture fair in October...{principal at assembly}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:34.39,signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\blur0.6\fs45\fnTalking to the Moon\c&HA5A5A6&\frz1.419\pos(528,213)}There is a preview \N\N{\c&H9C9C9E&}screening of the movie\N\N {\c&H949497&}in the media room. \N\N\N\h\h{\c&H79797B&}I'm going ahead.\N\N\N\N\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h{\c&H606061&}Chitanda
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.62,0:21:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine how anyone could have entered that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.51,0:21:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one could have.{sou da na}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except for one person: you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.40,0:21:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Just why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I didn't see that coming.{girls}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.87,0:21:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.05,0:21:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.73,0:21:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you can escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.69,0:21:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That was really cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn, that was one hell of an ending!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.09,0:22:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks like it was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.71,0:22:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah, to think it was the cameraman!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.41,0:22:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I heard ya figured it out in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.58,0:22:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.16,0:22:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, that endin' sure threw me fer a loop!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.26,0:22:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Ace Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.39,0:22:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ace detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.94,0:22:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome job!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.96,0:22:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it sure is a shame that the seventh character didn't like,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.18,0:22:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go nuts and massacre the rest of 'em when they found him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.58,0:22:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.45,0:22:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, much 'bliged!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.63,0:22:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Laters!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.86,0:22:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.32,0:22:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Nakajou!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.85,0:22:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.53,0:22:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your armpits reek.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.16,0:22:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.41,0:22:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{girl}Pretty nice, huh?{can't catch}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.82,0:22:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{sawa}{\an8}Don't you shower?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.48,0:22:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{naka}{\an8}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Haba wasn't a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.62,0:22:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.99,0:22:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.70,0:22:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was interesting. Didn't expect it to be the cameraman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.93,0:22:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what you were thinking earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.37,0:22:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't come up with it by that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.77,0:22:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.69,0:23:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh? They don't seem surprised at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.70,0:22:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's Houtarou for you.{satoshi}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.92,0:23:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah. Annoying as ever.{ibara}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.85,0:23:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, I guess this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.50,0:23:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.00,0:23:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.93,0:23:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.77,0:23:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.80,0:23:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.99,0:23:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, well done, Houtarou!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie's finished and the Empress approves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.24,0:23:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the viewers seem to like the surprise ending as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.74,0:23:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.72,0:23:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.25,0:23:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.86,0:23:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.70,0:23:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you came up with that conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.35,0:23:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.43,0:23:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.85,0:23:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you think of what Haba said?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.47,0:23:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haba?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.69,0:23:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.92,0:23:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rope didn't show up in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.87,0:24:10.63,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,300)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.63,0:24:14.63,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.63,0:24:19.72,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.11,0:24:40.87,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}This sprouting warmth confuses us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.95,0:24:51.80,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Don't you understand this feeling yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.38,0:24:57.89,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Normally such random glances hold no meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.89,0:25:03.22,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,450)\blur2}Isn't it the same when making friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.22,0:25:08.98,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}The little shooting stars we wish upon, vanishing into the dawn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.98,0:25:13.94,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}are a magic that only unfolds in the night
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.94,0:25:20.74,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.74,0:25:24.75,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,150)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.75,0:25:29.71,ED,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
